WEBVTT

00:05.655 --> 00:08.192
(quiet chatter)

00:10.464 --> 00:12.234
(sighs)

00:22.221 --> 00:24.024
I'm heading to Chapman Hills.

00:24.091 --> 00:27.732
Kyle has me reinspecting a place
I was at a week and a half ago.

00:29.235 --> 00:30.771
That's not right.

00:41.025 --> 00:42.762
(sniffs)

00:44.633 --> 00:46.002
Hey.

00:46.068 --> 00:48.140
Hey, Sam.

00:48.207 --> 00:50.678
You sent Jeanette
back to a place

00:50.745 --> 00:52.883
in Chapman Hills
that she was just at.

00:52.949 --> 00:54.419
Yeah.

00:54.485 --> 00:56.189
And...

00:56.255 --> 00:59.095
you sent me back
to Taverna Petraki.

00:59.161 --> 01:01.199
Things get reinspected, Sam.

01:01.266 --> 01:04.138
But they have to wait
their turn.

01:05.074 --> 01:06.610
Current wait time
in Lincoln County

01:06.677 --> 01:08.847
for reinspection
is almost eight months.

01:10.317 --> 01:12.421
(sighs) Sam...

01:12.488 --> 01:15.928
when you have my job,
you can do my job,

01:15.995 --> 01:19.168
but for now, why don't you worry
about doing your own job?

01:19.234 --> 01:20.738
Which you're good at,

01:20.805 --> 01:24.345
except for how you talk
to your boss.

01:32.896 --> 01:36.168
♪♪ ♪♪

01:44.786 --> 01:47.525
(footsteps overhead)

01:59.215 --> 02:01.419
My note...

02:02.856 --> 02:04.759
...is buried somewhere.

02:06.730 --> 02:08.701
Or sunk in a river.

02:11.940 --> 02:13.911
I'm not getting out of here.

02:15.881 --> 02:17.719
I'm never going home.

02:20.423 --> 02:23.296
What about the steak?

02:24.298 --> 02:25.467
What?

02:25.535 --> 02:27.739
Why do you keep thinking
about the steak?

02:27.806 --> 02:29.375
The steak? I'm not

02:29.442 --> 02:33.116
thinking a... Wh...

02:33.183 --> 02:36.155
Well, it's not
because I'm hungry.

02:36.222 --> 02:37.592
One thing you can't
complain about

02:37.659 --> 02:39.529
in this place is the food.

02:41.767 --> 02:43.604
Fine. You want
to talk about the steak?

02:43.671 --> 02:45.440
It irritates me.

02:46.375 --> 02:49.348
My daughter-in-law couldn't take
a simple compliment--

02:49.415 --> 02:50.718
or Ezra couldn't--

02:50.785 --> 02:53.624
without turning it
into an attack on her.

02:53.691 --> 02:56.296
He had to make it
into this huge thing.

02:56.363 --> 02:58.534
What exactly
was your compliment?

02:58.600 --> 03:00.705
(sighs) I told her she made

03:00.771 --> 03:02.909
the best kosher steak
I'd ever had.

03:02.975 --> 03:04.345
I complimented her cooking.

03:04.411 --> 03:08.219
By saying she made the best
kosher steak.

03:13.898 --> 03:17.204
Is there some difference
in kosher steaks?

03:17.271 --> 03:19.308
Yes. Yes, I get it.

03:19.375 --> 03:21.145
It could read as
a backhanded compliment.

03:21.212 --> 03:23.684
Anything could be read
as a backhanded compliment.

03:23.751 --> 03:25.487
It was a good steak,
and I said so.

03:25.555 --> 03:27.224
It was a good "kosher" steak.

03:27.291 --> 03:29.362
Okay. Okay, fine.

03:29.428 --> 03:32.268
Yeah, I-- You know,
I'm in an environment

03:32.334 --> 03:34.071
where I should realize
that everybody

03:34.137 --> 03:35.809
is sensitive and defensive,

03:35.875 --> 03:38.581
and if I'm a little more alert,
I just say "steak."

03:38.648 --> 03:41.654
I should've just said "steak."

03:41.721 --> 03:44.559
(sighs) God.

03:44.626 --> 03:46.930
What, does that make me
a bad father?

03:46.997 --> 03:50.270
Is that, is that what...

04:03.030 --> 04:04.966
(scraping resumes)

04:19.896 --> 04:22.033
(quiet chatter)

04:24.038 --> 04:26.910
(men chanting shaharith)

04:49.288 --> 04:51.560
CHARLIE:
He complained about a...

04:51.627 --> 04:52.762
a contribution you made.

04:52.829 --> 04:54.098
-What was that about?
-ALAN: Mm.

04:54.165 --> 04:56.302
His fucking yeshiva,

04:56.369 --> 04:58.273
in Israel.

04:58.340 --> 04:59.876
(sighs)

04:59.943 --> 05:02.648
After college,
Shoshana's in medical school,

05:02.715 --> 05:06.222
and he has to go to this
goddamn Orthodox yeshiva

05:06.289 --> 05:08.494
in Jerusalem. Fine.

05:08.561 --> 05:11.600
His second year,
Beth has a conference there,

05:11.666 --> 05:14.806
so we figure I'll come along,
and we'll visit Ezra.

05:14.873 --> 05:18.548
We get there, before we
see him at the yeshiva,

05:18.614 --> 05:21.954
he sends, uh,
a set of instructions

05:22.021 --> 05:25.628
to her on how she is
supposed to dress,

05:25.695 --> 05:29.502
like Beth doesn't know how
to dress around Orthodox Jews.

05:29.569 --> 05:32.942
So, she covers her hair,
every inch of her flesh.

05:33.009 --> 05:36.482
He takes us to meet the rebbe.
Forget your stereotypes.

05:36.550 --> 05:39.122
Young, hulking guy.

05:39.188 --> 05:41.059
Could've played football.

05:41.125 --> 05:43.463
He tells us that Ezra

05:43.531 --> 05:46.035
is a real ben torah.

05:46.102 --> 05:47.906
And Ezra's just beaming,

05:47.972 --> 05:51.312
like this is the best compliment
he's ever gotten.

05:51.378 --> 05:53.349
And the contribution?

05:53.416 --> 05:55.487
Ah.

05:55.555 --> 05:57.692
I was supposed to make
a contribution,

05:57.759 --> 05:59.361
right there in the office.

05:59.428 --> 06:01.231
This was made clear to me.

06:01.298 --> 06:04.940
So, I write a check for $1,000.

06:05.007 --> 06:07.378
But then...

06:07.444 --> 06:09.649
we're in the driveway,

06:09.716 --> 06:12.589
his mother is literally
dying in the house,

06:12.655 --> 06:15.093
and he says I don't respect him.

06:15.159 --> 06:18.633
I don't respect his choices.

06:18.700 --> 06:21.806
That I gave Shoshana, whatever,

06:21.873 --> 06:24.613
$40,000 a year
for medical school,

06:24.680 --> 06:28.152
and I gave his yeshiva
a paltry $1,000.

06:29.255 --> 06:30.825
Is yeshiva free?

06:30.891 --> 06:33.029
He never asked me to pay for it.

06:33.096 --> 06:35.233
He got a job and
a partial scholarship.

06:35.300 --> 06:38.707
-He asked you for a donation.
-And I made one.

06:39.643 --> 06:41.011
Do you know what it felt like

06:41.078 --> 06:43.483
to walk through
that yeshiva with Beth?

06:43.551 --> 06:45.487
Imagine if your son

06:45.555 --> 06:48.861
became a Scientologist,

06:48.928 --> 06:50.832
and you had to walk
through the...

06:50.898 --> 06:54.539
Scientology center with him,

06:54.605 --> 06:57.144
and at the end,
you gave a donation

06:57.210 --> 06:59.883
because you wanted
to make a gesture,

06:59.949 --> 07:02.522
and he took it as an insult?

07:02.588 --> 07:04.927
Alan,

07:04.993 --> 07:07.598
if you could talk
to Ezra right now,

07:07.665 --> 07:09.969
what would you say to him?

07:12.675 --> 07:15.581
"Ezra, you broke up our family.

07:17.852 --> 07:19.656
"You thought you had
all the answers.

07:19.723 --> 07:22.227
"You were so righteous.

07:22.293 --> 07:25.200
"You humiliated your mother.

07:25.267 --> 07:28.508
"You devastated her.

07:28.574 --> 07:30.210
"I want to s...

07:30.277 --> 07:31.780
"I want to say you killed her,

07:31.846 --> 07:34.653
"but I know that's not true.

07:34.719 --> 07:37.457
"All your mother wanted,
all she asked

07:37.525 --> 07:40.129
"was to be able to hold
the hands of both her children

07:40.196 --> 07:44.071
"in her dying moment,
and even this, you could not do.

07:44.138 --> 07:46.242
"Your way of looking
at the world

07:46.309 --> 07:48.513
"had to be the only way.

07:48.580 --> 07:50.951
Everyone else is wrong."

07:58.634 --> 08:01.506
You always thought
Ezra was obstinate,

08:01.573 --> 08:03.443
from the time
he was a little boy.

08:03.510 --> 08:05.147
I remember you talking about it.

08:05.213 --> 08:06.850
He was, always.

08:06.916 --> 08:10.156
You said, "Like his mother."

08:22.982 --> 08:25.253
("Mama, You've Been on My Mind"
by George Harrison playing)

08:32.368 --> 08:34.572
♪♪ Perhaps it's the color ♪♪

08:34.639 --> 08:36.744
♪♪ Of the sun cut flat ♪♪

08:36.810 --> 08:39.147
♪♪ And covering ♪♪

08:41.986 --> 08:45.527
♪♪ The crossroads
I'm standing at ♪♪

08:46.797 --> 08:49.068
♪♪ Or maybe it's the weather ♪♪

08:49.135 --> 08:51.807
♪♪ Or something like that ♪♪

08:51.873 --> 08:55.914
♪♪ Mama, you're just on my mind ♪♪

09:06.336 --> 09:10.276
♪♪ Someone who has had you
on his mind ♪♪

09:20.832 --> 09:22.936
♪♪ Maybe it's the weather ♪♪

09:23.003 --> 09:25.774
♪♪ Or something like that ♪♪

09:25.841 --> 09:30.016
♪♪ Mama, you're just
on my mind. ♪♪

09:46.215 --> 09:48.152
(engine starts)

10:07.792 --> 10:09.729
(engine starts)

10:26.295 --> 10:28.299
♪♪ ♪♪

10:37.752 --> 10:40.022
♪♪ ♪♪

10:49.609 --> 10:53.282
(winces)

11:08.212 --> 11:10.483
-(indistinct chatter)
-Here we go.

11:10.551 --> 11:13.623
BOTH:
Thank you, Grandma.

11:13.690 --> 11:15.126
-(laughter)
-(overlapping chatter)

11:15.193 --> 11:16.963
-TED: And cherries.
-SHOSHANA: Cherries?

11:17.030 --> 11:18.834
Bring that close for Alan.

11:18.900 --> 11:20.436
TED:
Here, buddy. Look at that.

11:20.504 --> 11:22.875
SHOSHANA:
Cherries...

11:38.072 --> 11:40.711
I always knew he was
more Beth's kid.

11:42.748 --> 11:44.519
Musical,

11:44.586 --> 11:46.756
into all that religious crap,

11:46.823 --> 11:48.860
even when he was little.

11:48.927 --> 11:51.232
At synagogue, with Beth,

11:51.299 --> 11:53.002
the both of them

11:53.068 --> 11:55.306
so sure of themselves,

11:55.373 --> 11:57.076
about everything.

11:58.046 --> 11:59.982
Shoshana was mine.

12:00.049 --> 12:02.487
Reasonable, became a therapist.

12:02.555 --> 12:06.128
Able to consider
everyone else's point of view.

12:10.538 --> 12:12.407
But, apparently,

12:12.473 --> 12:15.480
that story was bullshit.
Is that what you're saying?

12:15.548 --> 12:18.152
I'm not saying anything.

12:19.121 --> 12:22.093
You think maybe
I'm the obstinate one?

12:22.160 --> 12:25.534
I'm the asshole who always
thought he knew everything.

12:25.601 --> 12:28.540
Fuck you, Charlie.

12:29.676 --> 12:32.280
This could be it, Alan.

12:32.347 --> 12:34.384
Take a flyer.

12:41.532 --> 12:43.837
Fine. I had all the answers.

12:43.904 --> 12:45.774
I wrote the books.

12:45.841 --> 12:47.578
Rigid, know-it-all Ezra

12:47.644 --> 12:50.282
is as much my kid as Beth's.

12:52.420 --> 12:54.925
More.

13:01.940 --> 13:04.779
I did look down on him,

13:04.845 --> 13:07.417
on his religious choices.

13:09.989 --> 13:12.628
I have been blaming him.

13:12.695 --> 13:15.333
Blame and...?

13:18.940 --> 13:20.510
Contempt.

13:25.420 --> 13:27.591
Yes, contempt.

13:29.996 --> 13:33.435
He must've felt it,

13:33.503 --> 13:36.241
all of it.

13:36.308 --> 13:39.515
What do you want to say to him?

13:43.089 --> 13:44.959
I want to say...

13:46.864 --> 13:49.334
I want to say...

13:51.205 --> 13:53.308
"Why didn't you..."

13:54.912 --> 13:56.883
"Why couldn't y..."

13:56.949 --> 13:59.020
Okay.

14:01.392 --> 14:05.299
"I'm sorry, Ezra. I'm sorry."

14:05.366 --> 14:07.470
For...?

14:07.538 --> 14:10.443
"For not being...

14:10.510 --> 14:12.981
the father that I..."

14:15.888 --> 14:18.726
Charlie...

14:18.793 --> 14:21.499
I have been more understanding,

14:21.566 --> 14:26.008
more compassionate
to a fucking serial killer

14:26.074 --> 14:28.613
than I was to my own son.

14:34.759 --> 14:36.929
He has to hear this.

14:38.500 --> 14:40.236
From me.

14:42.307 --> 14:45.647
Too bad you're
going to die here.

15:01.178 --> 15:04.217
Broke. I need to borrow yours.

15:05.319 --> 15:06.656
Come in.

15:16.976 --> 15:18.546
(sniffs)

15:20.116 --> 15:22.454
You look exhausted.

15:22.522 --> 15:23.523
More than usual.

15:23.590 --> 15:25.059
(chuckles)

15:25.126 --> 15:27.230
I've got one more stack
to put up.

15:27.297 --> 15:28.534
Go home.

15:28.601 --> 15:31.238
I'll do it.

15:59.027 --> 16:01.298
♪♪ ♪♪

16:28.720 --> 16:31.526
Ezra, any news?

16:31.593 --> 16:33.563
-No.
-(sighs)

16:34.732 --> 16:36.201
Hashem yirachem.

16:49.862 --> 16:52.099
(indistinct chatter)

16:52.166 --> 16:54.404
♪♪ ♪♪

17:22.427 --> 17:25.166
-Hi.
-EZRA: Hey.

17:25.233 --> 17:28.372
I didn't know when you
were coming back. Sit.

17:32.815 --> 17:33.950
I have a treat.

17:34.017 --> 17:35.587
(bag rustling)

18:00.971 --> 18:03.208
♪♪ ♪♪

18:07.150 --> 18:09.287
(sighs)

18:38.078 --> 18:40.349
♪♪ ♪♪

18:54.210 --> 18:55.547
Kyle.

18:55.614 --> 18:57.283
-Sam. Hey.
-(chuckles)

18:57.350 --> 18:58.653
What are you doing here?

19:00.156 --> 19:01.291
JoJo's.

19:01.357 --> 19:02.828
Right. I-I never ate there.

19:02.894 --> 19:04.064
Is that-- Is it any good?

19:04.130 --> 19:06.035
Yeah. Yeah, it's good.

19:06.101 --> 19:07.738
Okay.

19:07.804 --> 19:10.544
Hey, you know the, uh,
Orchard Diner?

19:10.610 --> 19:12.413
They're in some kind of dispute
with Harris Carting.

19:12.480 --> 19:15.954
I-- They--
Their dumpster is just...

19:16.021 --> 19:17.892
You got to see this.

19:17.959 --> 19:19.394
Were you...

19:19.460 --> 19:21.533
You're not working, are you?
You weren't assigned...

19:21.599 --> 19:23.970
No. No, no. I just,
I just had dinner there.

19:24.036 --> 19:26.241
I just...

19:26.308 --> 19:28.613
Come on, man, you got to,
you got to see this.

19:30.115 --> 19:31.384
Okay.

19:33.121 --> 19:35.259
It's just over there.

19:35.326 --> 19:36.529
How you doing?

19:36.596 --> 19:38.667
-Ah, I'm a little hungry.
-Yeah?

19:38.734 --> 19:40.771
♪♪ Bonedigger, Bonedigger ♪♪

19:40.837 --> 19:42.908
♪♪ Dogs in the moonlight ♪♪

19:42.974 --> 19:45.714
♪♪ Far away in my well-lit door ♪♪

19:45.780 --> 19:48.052
♪♪ Mr. Beerbelly, Beerbelly... ♪♪

19:48.118 --> 19:50.389
(song continues over radio)

19:57.604 --> 19:59.675
♪♪ A man walks down
the street, he says ♪♪

19:59.741 --> 20:01.378
♪♪ "Why am I short
of attention?" ♪♪

20:01.445 --> 20:03.449
♪♪ Got a short little span
of attention ♪♪

20:03.516 --> 20:05.520
-♪♪ And, whoa. ♪♪
-(sighs)

20:17.276 --> 20:18.546
-Here?
-Yeah.

20:18.613 --> 20:19.815
Oh.

20:21.084 --> 20:22.687
-This?
-Yeah.

20:27.163 --> 20:28.365
This doesn't look so bad.

20:28.432 --> 20:31.304
Yeah, I guess they
must've just... (sniffs)

20:31.371 --> 20:33.175
cleaned it up,
like, a second ago,

20:33.242 --> 20:35.146
or something.

20:35.212 --> 20:38.018
-Okay.
-(scoffs)

20:38.085 --> 20:39.889
Well, all right.

20:39.955 --> 20:41.726
You...

20:41.793 --> 20:44.832
you shouldn't let restaurants
cut the reinspection line.

20:46.067 --> 20:49.207
What... (sighs)
What is wrong with you?

20:49.274 --> 20:51.478
(stammers)

20:52.748 --> 20:55.052
-Are you taking bribes?
-What?

20:55.987 --> 20:58.458
Sam, you are
completely out of line.

20:58.526 --> 21:00.128
Don't-don't talk to me
like I'm an idiot.

21:00.195 --> 21:03.703
If you think I'm taking bribes,
then you are a fucking idiot.

21:04.437 --> 21:07.476
(grunting)

21:10.550 --> 21:11.986
-(straining)
-Shut up.

21:12.053 --> 21:14.925
-Shut up, shut up. Shut up.
-(muffled shouting)

21:18.231 --> 21:20.469
(choking)

21:29.287 --> 21:32.727
I didn't like it when you read
that letter out loud.

21:40.944 --> 21:43.014
(breathing heavily)

21:54.571 --> 21:57.711
(clock ticking)

22:13.943 --> 22:16.047
(panting)

22:45.005 --> 22:47.076
♪♪ ♪♪

23:05.681 --> 23:10.122
(reciting Kaddish)

23:13.195 --> 23:15.365
(stammers)

23:15.432 --> 23:17.771
Kaddish?

23:22.046 --> 23:25.452
(door creaking)

23:46.562 --> 23:48.866
(clock ticking)

24:04.197 --> 24:06.702
(sighs)

24:27.276 --> 24:29.781
♪♪ Almost heaven ♪♪

24:31.686 --> 24:34.524
♪♪ West Virginia ♪♪

24:35.794 --> 24:38.833
♪♪ Blue Ridge Mountain ♪♪

24:38.900 --> 24:41.138
♪♪ Shenandoah ♪♪

24:41.204 --> 24:43.976
♪♪ River ♪♪

24:46.048 --> 24:49.020
♪♪ Life is old there ♪♪

24:49.087 --> 24:52.794
♪♪ Older than the trees ♪♪

24:52.861 --> 24:56.903
♪♪ Younger than the mountains ♪♪

24:56.969 --> 25:00.442
♪♪ Growing like a breeze ♪♪

25:00.510 --> 25:03.817
♪♪ Country roads ♪♪

25:03.883 --> 25:07.524
♪♪ Take me home ♪♪

25:07.590 --> 25:11.164
♪♪ To the place ♪♪

25:11.231 --> 25:14.671
♪♪ I belong ♪♪

25:14.738 --> 25:17.944
♪♪ West Virginia ♪♪

25:18.011 --> 25:21.418
♪♪ Mountain mama ♪♪

25:21.484 --> 25:24.591
♪♪ Take me home ♪♪

25:25.960 --> 25:30.001
♪♪ Country roads. ♪♪

25:44.163 --> 25:47.169
♪♪ ♪♪

26:16.495 --> 26:18.766
♪♪ ♪♪

26:23.141 --> 26:24.945
MR. BUCHELLA (over phone):
Hello?

26:25.012 --> 26:27.518
SAM:
Hey, Mr. Buchella. It's Sam.

26:27.584 --> 26:29.789
Oh. Hi, Sam.

26:29.855 --> 26:31.357
How are you?

26:31.424 --> 26:33.596
I'm bad.

26:33.663 --> 26:37.036
Oh. I'm sorry to hear that.

26:37.102 --> 26:39.440
I was thinking
about your question,

26:39.508 --> 26:43.014
and I'd be glad to do it,
to be your therapist.

26:44.651 --> 26:47.022
Okay. Wh-When can we start?

26:47.089 --> 26:49.127
How about next, uh, Tuesday?

26:49.194 --> 26:51.499
Is 4:30 okay?

26:51.565 --> 26:52.634
Sure.

26:52.701 --> 26:54.605
We can meet at my house.

26:54.671 --> 26:56.842
The sessions will be 45 minutes,

26:56.908 --> 27:00.248
and the charge
is $125 per session.

27:01.719 --> 27:03.388
That's a good deal.

27:03.455 --> 27:07.095
MR. BUCHELLA: Well, great,
great. Well, see you then.

27:11.204 --> 27:13.241
(door unlocks)

27:28.573 --> 27:31.477
I wasn't mekayem kibud av va'em.

27:31.545 --> 27:34.116
-That's not true.
-Well...

27:35.219 --> 27:37.423
When Mom died,

27:37.490 --> 27:40.797
he was... (sighs)

27:40.864 --> 27:43.234
he was so harsh,

27:43.301 --> 27:45.706
and I...

27:47.376 --> 27:48.879
Chava, I...

27:50.583 --> 27:53.221
I was just mad at him.

27:55.226 --> 27:56.862
That's all.

27:58.833 --> 28:01.137
And now...

28:19.340 --> 28:21.444
(gate creaks)

28:39.514 --> 28:42.052
(snoring)

29:04.598 --> 29:06.902
♪♪ ♪♪

29:35.259 --> 29:36.828
Dr. Strauss.

29:51.892 --> 29:54.129
Do you play ping-pong?

29:55.432 --> 29:56.568
Yes.

29:56.635 --> 29:59.406
Do you want to play ping-pong?

30:00.710 --> 30:02.379
Okay.

30:08.325 --> 30:10.395
(chain rattling)

